sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant API as API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP MySQL TLS1.2+
    participant WFC as Workflow Controller<br/>8887/TCP gRPC TLS1.2+
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Pod as Pipeline Pod
    participant S3 as Minio/S3<br/>9000/443 HTTP/S
    participant PA as Persistence Agent
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata<br/>9090/TCP gRPC TLS1.2+

    %% Flow 1: Pipeline Submission and Execution
    Note over User,MLMD: Flow 1: Pipeline Submission and Execution

    User->>Route: POST /apis/v1beta1/pipelines<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OAuth)
    Route->>OAuth: Forward HTTPS request<br/>TLS 1.3
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OAuth token<br/>Check OpenShift RBAC
    OAuth->>API: Forward to API Server<br/>HTTP (internal)
    API->>DB: Store pipeline metadata<br/>MySQL + Password Auth
    DB-->>API: Confirm storage

    API->>WFC: Create Workflow CR<br/>gRPC + mTLS
    WFC->>K8s: Create Workflow resources<br/>HTTPS + ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>WFC: Workflow created

    WFC->>Pod: Launch pipeline pod<br/>via Kubernetes
    Pod->>S3: Store/retrieve artifacts<br/>Access Key/Secret
    S3-->>Pod: Artifact data

    PA->>DB: Sync workflow state<br/>MySQL + Password
    Pod->>MLMD: Track artifact metadata<br/>gRPC + mTLS
    MLMD->>DB: Store metadata<br/>MySQL + Password

    Pod-->>User: Pipeline execution results<br/>via API queries

    %% Flow 2: Artifact Metadata Tracking
    Note over User,MLMD: Flow 2: Artifact Metadata Tracking (Detail)

    User->>Route: GET /apis/v1beta1/artifacts<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Route->>OAuth: Forward HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.3
    OAuth->>API: Validated request
    API->>MLMD: Query artifact lineage<br/>gRPC + mTLS
    MLMD->>DB: Retrieve metadata<br/>MySQL + Password
    DB-->>MLMD: Metadata records
    MLMD-->>API: Artifact lineage
    API-->>OAuth: JSON response
    OAuth-->>Route: Forward response
    Route-->>User: Artifact metadata

    %% Flow 3: DSPA Custom Resource Reconciliation
    Note over User,K8s: Flow 3: DSPA CR Reconciliation

    User->>K8s: kubectl apply -f dspa.yaml<br/>HTTPS + Bearer Token
    K8s->>Controller: Watch event: DSPA created
    Controller->>K8s: Create Deployments, Services, Routes<br/>HTTPS + ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>Controller: Resources created
    Controller->>K8s: Update DSPA status<br/>Ready condition
